Feature: Managing Project Folder

This feature is designed to test the main possible, but basic operations a user can perform
in order to manage project folder. Some fundamental connections/ assignments with other CDB objects
might also be tested. Further possible connections/ assignments are tested in the respective feature.

Background:
    Given a project exists


Scenario Outline: Create New Project Folder
    When <role> creates a new project folder
    Then a new project folder is <creation>

    Examples:
        | role            | creation      |
        | Projektleiter   | generated     |
        | Projektmitglied | generated     |
        | nobody          | not generated |


Scenario Outline: Change Project Folder
    Given a project folder exists
    When <role> changes this project folder
    Then the changed project folder is <status>

    Examples:
        | role            | status    |
        | Projektleiter   | saved     |
        | nobody          | not saved |


Scenario Outline: Copy Project Folder
    Given a project folder exists
    When <role> copies this project folder
    Then the project folder is <status>

    Examples:
        | role            | status     |
        | Projektleiter   | copied     |
        | Projektmitglied | copied     |
        | nobody          | not copied |


Scenario Outline: Delete Project Folder
    Given a project folder exists
        When <role> deletes this project folder
        Then the project folder is <status>

        Examples:
        | role            | status      |
        | Projektleiter   | deleted     |
        | Projektmitglied | deleted     |
        | nobody          | not deleted |


Scenario Outline: Allocate A Document To A Project Folder
    Given a project folder exists
        And a document exists
        When <role> allocates this document to the project folder
        Then the document is <status> to the project folder

        Examples:
        | role            | status        |
        | Projektleiter   | allocated     |
        | Projektmitglied | allocated     |
        | nobody          | not allocated |


Scenario Outline: Delete Project Folder Allocation Of A Document
    Given a project folder exists
        And a document exists
        And it is allocated to the project folder
    When <role> deletes this allocation of the document to the project folder
    Then the allocation of the document to the project folder is <status>

    Examples:
        | role            | status      |
        | Projektleiter   | deleted     |
        | Projektmitglied | deleted     |
        | nobody          | not deleted |
